For the last week it has been  muddy but we have not had much  rain. Our snow which for a week previous  afforded quite good sleighing has all disapeared  We are in need of rain and hope that winter will not set in until we have our usual fall rains. There was a Lord Templars Convention at Lowville yesterday and today I did not attend. Prof. E.W. Mason G.W.S lectured here Monday eve. on his way to Lowville. We had a good meeting and initiated 15 after the lecture. Last  evening the initiated at Lowville 69 after the evening meeting!   Married;     
  Last Sabbath, by Rev. J.W. Roberts, Mr. John C. Jones to Miss Lucina Allen This took place in the M.E. Church after the services in the morning and your brother was groomsman. That is about as near as I expect to come to being married for the present - near enough was'nt it?         
  There is a good deal of sickness  about here - mostly feavers. I am  blessed with good health. When do you expect to come home?
